						               													<description>In Battle of the Beetles green and red beetles fight among themselves. Your goal is to be the last player making a valid action. In order to play Battle of the Beetles you need a modified 7 x 7 board with 44 cells, 28 white rings (&amp;ldquo;eggshells&amp;rdquo;) and 28 rounder counters (14 green and 14 red &amp;ldquo;beetles&amp;rdquo;)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each turn a player must perform one of the following actions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Remove the eggshell from one of your eggs. The removed eggshell is out of the game.&amp;#10;    Capture an enemy beetle. A born beetle makes a capture in two steps: First it moves forward to a cell adjacent to it. Then it flies to a cell occupied by an enemy beetle which removed from the game. The beetle flies exactly as a knight moves in chess. &amp;#10;    Capture a friendly beetle according to the rules mentioned above. This action can only be carried out if the player is not able to perform the aforementioned actions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player cannot make any of these actions in his/her turn, he/she loses.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
